      "source": [
        "## Visualize Topics\n",
        "Now, let's create a facet bar graph for topics 2, 5, 10, and 15, visualizing the top 10 words and their probabilities for each topic."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vs3-zONxcld4"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "74401bd7"
      },
      "source": [
        "For that, we will prepare the data for plotting by converting the topic words and probabilities into a pandas DataFrame. This involves iterating through target topic IDs, extracting top words, and structuring them into a list of dictionaries before converting to a DataFrame.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "c23cad4d",
        "outputId": "1fd5fdea-1309-4bd8-b185-48ffb43ab03c"
      },
      "source": [
        "topic_data = []\n",
        "target_topic_ids = [2, 5, 10, 15]\n",
        "\n",
        "for topic_id in target_topic_ids:\n",
        "    # Retrieve the top 10 words and their probabilities for the current topic\n",
        "    topic_terms = lda_model.show_topic(topic_id, topn=10)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for word, prob in topic_terms:\n",
        "        topic_data.append({\n",
        "            'Topic ID': topic_id,\n",
        "            'Word': word,\n",
        "            'Probability': prob\n",
        "        })\n",
        "\n",
        "df_topic_words = pd.DataFrame(topic_data)\n",
        "print(\"DataFrame 'df_topic_words' created successfully with topic words and probabilities.\")\n",
        "print(df_topic_words.head())"
      ],
